Melania and Donald Trump extend their greetings to all Jewish people on Yom Kippur, the holiest day in the Jewish faith. They acknowledge that Yom Kippur is a day of atonement, prayer, and fasting, and marks the end of the Ten Days of Repentance. They emphasize the importance of drawing closer to God through the practice of teshuva, as mentioned in Leviticus. Melania and Donald Trump pray that everyone is inscribed in the Book of Life and hope that this period of reflection and repentance strengthens their relationship with God. They send their best wishes for a meaningful Yom Kippur and a Gmar Chatima Tova.